  {
    "type": "callout",
    "text": "Definition: Accumulation of excessive fluid in the interstitial space.\n• Pitting Oedema: Indentation persists after pressure is applied (Low protein fluid).\n• Non-Pitting Oedema: No indentation (High protein fluid / Lymphatic obstruction / Myxoedema)."
  },
